title: cuDNN launch failure

labels.name: howtousedlc
labels.description: issue regarding the use of DeepLabCut

body:
Thanks for opening this issue, and thanks for using DeepLabCut (we hope you are enjoying it ;). Please fill out the template completely, including the full "traceback" and input code that you ran to hit this error. **Your Operating system and DeepLabCut version** Please state your operating system, env, and which version of DeepLabCut you are using. Example: Ubuntu 16.04 LTS, with an Anaconda Env, & DeepLabCut1.x or 2 Please complete the following information about your system: OS: [e.g. MacOS, Windows 10, etc] windows 10 DeepLabCut Version: [e.g. 2.2] (please check with import deeplabcut, deeplabcut.__version__) 2.2b7 Anaconda env used: DLC-GPU **Describe the problem** When trying to train my model I am receiving the error: InternalError (see above for traceback): cuDNN launch failure : input shape([32,512,32,55]) filter shape([3,3,512,512]) Alongside: Allocator (GPU_0_bfc) ran out of memory trying to allocate 1.33GiB. The machine I am using appears to have enough memory (totalMemory: 24.00GiB freeMemory: 20.00GiB). I have checked my tensor flow version and received this error with both version 1.12 and 1.13. Any ideas on why I am having these issues and how they can be resolved? Please note I am using the GUI. Please place code inside this:
